 blog of gardener Dorothy Ernst.  Dorothy believes the garden contributes to our overall well-being – physically, mentally, emotionally and spiritually and she provides services in garden mentoring and coaching, horticultural therapy and spiritual gardening.  Planting my Voice is a place where she can share her life experiences as a gardener.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Post-cropped.jpg" rel="shadowbox[post-5879];player=img;"><img class="size-full wp-image-5880 aligncenter" title="Planting my Voice" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Post-cropped.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="480" /></a></p>\n<p>Dorothy contacted WebDevStudios because she had a WordPress.com website that was not meeting her needs.  She loved the simplicity of WordPress&#8217; admin panel, but felt restricted as to what she could do with it.  We worked with Dorothy to make a great new blog that highlighted her blog posts as well as her beautiful photography.</p>\n<p>We also had the chance to work with some great WordPress products on this project. Dorothy&#8217;s theme was designed using <a title="iThemes Builder" href="http://webdevstudios.com/go/ithemes-builder/">iThemes Builder</a> which makes it easy to create customized website layouts and page templates.  Builder also has some great features for customizing a WordPress website including a layout editor, child theme support, and style manager.</p>\n<p>Her new website is also hosted through <a title="Page.ly" href="http://webdevstudios.com/go/pagely/">Page.ly</a>.  Page.ly provides <a title="Page.ly Hosting Plans" href="http://page.ly/plans-pricing/detail/">amazing managed hosting plans</a> with secured hosting through Firehost.com. They also provide automatic WordPress core, plugin upgrades and nightly backups.</p>\n<p><a title="Planting My Voice" href="http://PlantingMyVoice.com">PlantingMyVoice.com</a> now has a great unique style along with a fully secure and managed home. We love the new website and hope you do too!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://webdevstudios.com/2011/04/08/plantingmyvoice-com-powered-by-ithemes-builder-page-ly/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:44:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"WDS Welcomes Brian Layman!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"http://webdevstudios.com/2011/03/30/wds-welcomes-brian-layman/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"http://webdevstudios.com/2011/03/30/wds-welcomes-brian-layman/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 30 Mar 2011 14:00:07 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WebDevStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=5830";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s